      "id": "t61",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "How long does it take to get monetized on YouTube?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t62",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Most channels reach the 1,000 subscriber and 4,000 watch hour threshold in 6–18 months with consistent posting, though it varies widely by niche and content quality."
    },
    {
      "id": "t63",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Can you lose YouTube monetization?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t64",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Yes — policy violations, copyright strikes, or falling below engagement thresholds can result in demonetization. Maintaining advertiser-friendly content is essential."
    },
    {
      "id": "t65",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "What's the difference between CPM and RPM?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t66",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "CPM is what advertisers pay YouTube per 1,000 impressions. RPM is what you receive per 1,000 views — approximately 55% of CPM multiplied by your ad impression rate."
    },
